OL,3,CFormer sub-postmaster 'honoured' to
OL,4,Cget degree from Bangor University
OL,6,FMr Thomas was convicted for theft and
OL,7,Ffalse accounting along with one of
OL,8,Fmore than 700 sub-postmasters.
OL,10,FHe was wrongly accused of stealing
OL,11,F#48,000 from the Post Office due to
OL,12,Fflawed information from the
OL,13,Forganisation's Horizon computer system.
OL,15,FMr Thomas was disqualified as a
OL,16,Fcouncillor, jailed for nine months and
OL,17,Fhis daughter was forced to sell her
OL,18,Fhome to pay legal costs.
